The paper discusses cryptographic protocols for electronic auctions, with a focus on privacy. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and game theory (cs.GT). The use of homomorphic operations and distributed encryption suggests a connection to cryptography and computational complexity (cs.CC). The discussion of verifiability and attacks on non-repudiation suggest a connection to distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the use of authentication and privacy issues suggest a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
